Quantifying the strength of a dependence between two continuous random variables is an essential task in data science [wang:09:divergence]. Due to its non-parametric nature, and hence its ability to measure complex non-linear dependencies, mutual information is ideal for this task [cover:06:elements], which is why it is routinely applied for challenging settings such as gene network inference.